Attach numismatic monograms as members

comments.body: @hackmastera Changed "Attach Monogram" to "Attach Child" As to the larger question, I don't think that attaching monograms as members will be a problem. Ilya said that it is rare for a monogram to be shared among Issues; case in point, monogram images are labeled by issue number. If it becomes an issue, we can modify the UI so that a existing monogram can be attached. Like what we do for geo resources: I don't think that it's worth spending time on it until it becomes a user request.

Maybe I'm misremembering and it's only a file set that is not allowed to have more than one parent. Perhaps @tpendragon could arbitrate here. 

Otherwise 👍 on the edits. There's a failing test.

Even if having two parents is frowned upon, I don't think that's a show stopper here. Neither Alan or Ilya was bothered by uploading an image twice in the rare event of a duplicated monogram. The other option is to go back to where we were before and iterate on a convoluted interface-- how does one choose a monogram from a list of thousands, mostly without useful titles? -- to support an edge case.

figgy.title: Convert color space to SRGB through VIPS

comments.body:
Do you have a test recommendation? I don't know much about color spaces. Presumably there's some tool that will analyze the embedded space of an image and tell you what it is.

Now CI VIPS matches the version installed on the servers. Before it was older on CI.

Is this helpful? It says

```You can test for the presence of an embedded profile with vips_image_get_typeof() with VIPS_META_ICC_NAME as an argument. This will return GType 0 if there is no profile.```

https://libvips.github.io/libvips/API/current/libvips-colour.html#vips-icc-import

@hackmastera Yeah, we do that to see if there's a profile, but I can't really tell what the profile is. Maybe I can check to see if the profile's changed, but I'm hesitant to check what the profile actually is in case it changes in a future version or something.

figgy.title: GoogleDrive not working for numismatics user

comments.body:
By introducing error logging and using a set of Google test credentials, I am now able to reproduce this:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1443986/82358736-f160f080-99d4-11ea-852f-4cb6ebd498f9.png)

I've managed to restructure the code base with https://github.com/jrgriffiniii/browse-everything-redux-react/tree/fixes-firefox-76, but I am still receiving the following error with a separate set of testing credentials from Google:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1443986/82377132-38f57580-99f1-11ea-8f2a-f320e5665f49.png)

This still *does* work for me in the staging environment, but given that the Google JavaScript which transmits these AJAX requests is minified, I cannot trace exactly where I can disable the header warning which I *suspect* is the problem:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1443986/82377252-66daba00-99f1-11ea-800a-45e54315bfab.png)

I've managed to get this working with a local, decompressed copy of the `gapi` JavaScript file. I'm going to attempt extending the configuration for Webpack in order to ensure that this can be consistently resolved by apps consuming the React UI.
